This software launches Modbus Process Simulator v1.9.0 (process simulator).
Arguments in this program include:
-install (optional): This flag is to tell program to install itself if it is not installed.
-loadFile (optional): This argument is to load a project file at launch. Example usage:
	-loadFile="your/absolute/path/name/example.xmpp"
Make sure the path name is the absolute path, or you will get an error message back.
-portNumber (optional): This argument sets the initial TCP/IP port number to a number between 0 and 65536. Example usage:
	-portNumber=1234
Make sure the port you choose is not a reserved port number or in use. If a number is not given, an error message will be returned.
If this argument is not given or an invalid port value is given, then the port number will be set to 502, or the value in the initial project file loaded.
-help (optional): Displays the help message.
